Name: WindVxi
Description: Nominally downwind component of the hub-height wind velocity

Name: WindVyi
Description: Cross-wind component of the hub-height wind velocity

Name: WindVzi
Description: Vertical component of the hub-height wind velocity

Name: TotWindV
Description: Total hub-height wind velocity magnitude

Name: HorWindV
Description: Horizontal hub-height wind velocity magnitude

Name: HorWndDir
Description: Horizontal hub-height wind direction.  Please note that FAST  uses the opposite sign convention that AeroDyn uses.  Put a "-", "_", "m", or "M" character in front of this variable name if you want to use the AeroDyn convention.

Name: VerWndDir
Description: Vertical hub-height wind direction
Convention: About an axis orthogonal to the zi-axis and the HorWindV-vector

Name: TipDxc1
Description: Blade 1 out-of-plane tip deflection (relative to the undeflected position)

Name: TipDyc1
Description: Blade 1 in-plane tip deflection (relative to the undeflected position)

Name: TipDzc1
Description: Blade 1 axial tip deflection (relative to the undeflected position)
Convention: Directed along the zc1- and zb1-axes

Name: TipDxb1
Description: Blade 1 flapwise tip deflection (relative to the undeflected position)

Name: TipDyb1
Description: Blade 1 edgewise tip deflection (relative to the undeflected position)

Name: TipALxb1
Description: Blade 1 local flapwise tip acceleration (absolute)

Name: TipALyb1
Description: Blade 1 local edgewise tip acceleration (absolute)

Name: TipALzb1
Description: Blade 1 local axial tip acceleration (absolute)

Name: TipRDxb1
Description: Blade 1 roll (angular/rotational) tip deflection (relative to the undeflected position). In ADAMS, it is output as an Euler angle computed as the 3rd rotation in the yaw-pitch-roll rotation sequence. It is not output as an Euler angle in FAST, which assumes small blade deflections, so that the rotation sequence does not matter.

Name: TipRDyb1
Description: Blade 1 pitch (angular/rotational) tip deflection (relative to the undeflected position). In ADAMS, it is output as an Euler angle computed as the 2nd rotation in the yaw-pitch-roll rotation sequence. It is not output as an Euler angle in FAST, which assumes small blade deflections, so that the rotation sequence does not matter.

Name: TipRDzc1
Description: Blade 1 torsional tip deflection (relative to the undeflected position). This output will always be zero for FAST simulation results. Use it for examining blade torsional deflections of ADAMS simulations run using ADAMS datasets created using the FAST-to-ADAMS preprocessor. In ADAMS, it is output as an Euler angle computed as the 1st rotation in the yaw-pitch-roll rotation sequence.  Please note that this output uses the opposite of the sign convention used for blade pitch angles.

Name: TipClrnc1
Description: Blade 1 tip-to-tower clearance estimate. This is computed as the perpendicular distance from the yaw axis to the tip of blade 1 when the blade tip is below the yaw bearing. When the tip of blade 1 is above the yaw bearing, it is computed as the absolute distance from the yaw bearing to the blade tip. Please note that you should reduce this value by the tower radius to obtain the actual tower clearance.

Name: Spn1RDxb2
Description: Blade 2 local roll (angular/rotational)  deflection (relative to the undeflected position) of span station 1. In ADAMS, it is output as an Euler angle computed as the 3rd rotation in the yaw-pitch-roll rotation sequence. It is not output as an Euler angle in FAST, which assumes small blade deflections, so that the rotation sequence does not matter.

Name: Spn1RDyb2
Description: Blade 2 local pitch (angular/rotational) deflection (relative to the undeflected position) of span station 1. In ADAMS, it is output as an Euler angle computed as the 2nd rotation in the yaw-pitch-roll rotation sequence. It is not output as an Euler angle in FAST, which assumes small blade deflections, so that the rotation sequence does not matter.

Name: Spn1RDzb2
Description: Blade 2 local torsional (angular/rotational) deflection (relative to the undeflected position) of span station 1. This output will always be zero for FAST simulation results. Use it for examining blade torsional deflections of ADAMS simulations run using ADAMS datasets created using the FAST-to-ADAMS preprocessor. In ADAMS, it is output as an Euler angle computed as the 1st rotation in the yaw-pitch-roll rotation sequence.  Please note that this output uses the opposite of the sign convention used for blade pitch angles.

Name: NacYawErr
Description: Nacelle yaw error estimate. This is computed as follows: NacYawErr = HorWndDir - YawPzn - YawBrRDzt - PtfmRDzi. This estimate is not accurate instantaneously in the presence of significant tower deflection or platform angular (rotational) displacement since the angles used in the computation are not all defined about the same axis of rotation. Name: LSShftFxa
Description: Low-speed shaft thrust force (this is constant along the shaft and is equivalent to the rotor thrust force)
Convention: Directed along the xa- and xs-axes

Name: LSShftFya
Description: Rotating low-speed shaft shear force (this is constant along the shaft)

Name: LSShftFza
Description: Rotating low-speed shaft shear force (this is constant along the shaft)

Name: LSShftFys
Description: Nonrotating low-speed shaft shear force (this is constant along the shaft)

Name: LSShftFzs
Description: Nonrotating low-speed shaft shear force (this is constant along the shaft)

Name: LSShftMxa
Description: Low-speed shaft torque (this is constant along the shaft and is equivalent to the rotor torque)

Name: LSSTipMya
Description: Rotating low-speed shaft bending moment at the shaft tip (teeter pin for 2-blader, apex of rotation for 3-blader)

Name: LSSTipMza
Description: Rotating low-speed shaft bending moment at the shaft tip (teeter pin for 2-blader, apex of rotation for 3-blader)

Name: LSSTipMys
Description: Nonrotating low-speed shaft bending moment at the shaft tip (teeter pin for 2-blader, apex of rotation for 3-blader)

Name: LSSTipMzs
Description: Nonrotating low-speed shaft bending moment at the shaft tip (teeter pin for 2-blader, apex of rotation for 3-blader)

Name: CThrstAzm
Description: Azimuth location of the center of thrust. This is estimated using values of LSSTipMys, LSSTipMzs, and RotThrust.

Name: CThrstRad
Description: Dimensionless radial (arm) location of the center of thrust. This is estimated using values of LSSTipMys, LSSTipMzs, and RotThrust. (nondimensionalized using the undeflected tip radius normal to the shaft and limited to values between 0 and 1 (inclusive))
Convention: Always positive (directed radially outboard at azimuth angle CThrstAzm)

Name: RotPwr
Description: Rotor power (this is equivalent to the low-speed shaft power)

Name: RotCq
Description: Rotor torque coefficient (this is equivalent to the low-speed shaft torque coefficient)

Name: RotCp
Description: Rotor power coefficient (this is equivalent to the low-speed shaft power coefficient)

Name: RotCt
Description: Rotor thrust coefficient (this is equivalent to the low-speed shaft thrust coefficient)

Name: LSSGagMya
Description: Rotating low-speed shaft bending moment at the shaft's strain gage (shaft strain gage located by input ShftGagL)

Name: LSSGagMza
Description: Rotating low-speed shaft bending moment at the shaft's strain gage (shaft strain gage located by input ShftGagL)

Name: LSSGagMys
Description: Nonrotating low-speed shaft bending moment at the shaft's strain gage (shaft strain gage located by input ShftGagL)

Name: LSSGagMzs
Description: Nonrotating low-speed shaft bending moment at the shaft's strain gage (shaft strain gage located by input ShftGagL)

Name: HSShftTq
Description: High-speed shaft torque (this is constant along the shaft)
Convention: Same sign as LSShftTq / RotTorq / LSShftMxa / LSShftMxs / LSSGagMxa / LSSGagMxs

Name: HSShftPwr
Description: High-speed shaft power

Name: HSShftCq
Description: High-speed shaft torque coefficient

Name: HSShftCp
Description: High-speed shaft power coefficient

Name: GenTq
Description: Electrical generator torque
Convention: Positive reflects power extracted and negative represents a motoring-up situation (power input)

Name: GenPwr
Description: Electrical generator power

Name: GenCq
Description: Electrical generator torque coefficient

Name: GenCp
Description: Electrical generator power coefficient

Name: HSSBrTq
Description: High-speed shaft brake torque (i.e., the moment applied to the high-speed shaft by the brake)

Name: RFrlBrM
Description: Rotor-furl bearing moment

Name: TFrlBrM
Description: Tail-furl bearing moment

Name: TFinAlpha
Description: Tail fin angle of attack. This is the angle between the relative velocity of the wind-inflow at the tail fin center-of-pressure and the tail fin chordline.
Convention: About the tail fin z-axis, which is the axis in the tail fin plane normal to the chordline

Name: TFinCLift
Description: Tail fin dimensionless lift coefficient

Name: TFinCDrag
Description: Tail fin dimensionless drag coefficient

Name: TFinDnPrs
Description: Tail fin dynamic pressure, equal to 1/2*AirDens*Vrel^2 where Vrel is the relative velocity of the wind-inflow at the tail fin center-of-pressure

Name: TFinCPFx
Description: Tangential aerodynamic force at the tail fin center-of-pressure
Convention: Directed along the tail fin x-axis, which is the axis along the chordline, positive towards the trailing edge

Name: TFinCPFy
Description: Normal aerodynamic force at the tail fin center-of-pressure
Convention: Directed along the tail fin y-axis, which is orthogonal to the tail fin plane
